The paper proposes a probabilistic graphical annotation model for inferring ground truth and annotator behavior in the context of data labeling. This involves both discrete and continuous application scenarios, which suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions classifying scenes and rating videos, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of probabilistic models and inference also suggests information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL) as potential sub-categories.
